  "prompt": "Which song is being played in movie creed when creed's went to lower the volume?",
  "response": "In the movie **\"Creed\" (2015)**, during the scene where Adonis Creed lowers the volume, the song playing is **\"Ready to Go\" by Republica**. This track is prominently featured in several training and motivational sequences throughout the film, helping to underscore Adonis's determination and drive as he prepares for his boxing career.\n\n**\"Ready to Go\" by Republica** is an energetic and uplifting song that perfectly complements the themes of perseverance and ambition depicted in \"Creed.\" Its inclusion in the film adds to the intensity of the training montages and highlights Adonis's commitment to honoring his father's legacy while forging his own path in the boxing world.\n\nIf you're looking to revisit the song, it's part of Republica's self-titled album released in 1996 and has been widely used in various media for its motivational vibe.",
